        "message": "LU-19474 kfilnd: Replay early RX events\n\nMessages that are received from a \"new\" kfilnd peer are currently\n(silently) dropped. This was due to historical concerns about the\ninitiator of a message using an invalid session key. LUS-12317\nmodified the bulk protocol to store the session key in the bulk\nrequest message, and use that key to generate the RKEY for the RMA\noperation. This means we can now replay the TN_EVENT_RX_OK, and we can\nalso drop the session key validation that was added in LUS-12317\n(tn_session_key_is_valid()). The session key validation was never\nnecessary. For bulk V1 protocol, the keys will never mismatch, and\nwith V2 it shouldn't be possible to reuse an RKEY due to a change in\nthe kfilnd_peer session key.\n\nAllowing replay of TN_EVENT_RX_OK events has two benefits. The first\nis that immediate message transactions now have a chance to succeed\nwhereas previously they would have silently failed. The silent\nfailures force us to wait for upper level timeouts to expire before\napplications could make forward progress. The second is that some bulk\ntransaction failures no longer fail silently. This enhancement can\nallow bulk operations to be re-tried more quickly rather than waiting\nfor the bulk timeout to expire.\n\nThis patch modifies some debug statements to include the NID of target\npeer.\n\nAn old outdated comment has been removed from kfilnd_tn_state_idle().\n\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-12877\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Ide1f48e02e2126b83222dbb23a5d8f924fe40fef\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61823\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander.boyko@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Ron Gredvig <ron.gredvig@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
